body:
Never needed to do this before, but I am looking to rename some inout signals in a "fancy" way and the Verilog port expressions seems to support what I need. Icarus supports but Verilator throws a syntax error. (see the chip module). Is this a case of using some weird corner case of the standard that nobody uses? (I haven't needed it in 25 years of design).

Test Case:

```verilog

module top();

   initial
     begin
	$dumpvars();
	#100
	  $finish;
     end

   wire x,y;

   assign x = 1'b0;

   chip chip(/*AUTOINST*/
	     // Inouts
	     .x				(x),
	     .y				(y));

endmodule

module chip(.x(a), .y(b));

   inout wire a;
   inout wire b;

   padring padring(/*AUTOINST*/
		   // Inouts
		   .a			(a),
		   .b			(b));

endmodule // blackbox

module padring(inout a, inout b);

   wire sela = 1'b0;
   wire selb = 1'b1;

   assign a = sela ? 1'b1 : 1'bz;
   assign b = selb ? 1'b1 : 1'bz;


endmodule
```
